tgl_active_number_color="#ffffff" one_active="true" active_tab="1" title_size="21px"][vc_accordion_tab title="What is freelancing?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1543562657523{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Freelancing occurs when someone offers his or her services for an agreed period in return for a fee. Freelancers (also known as contractors or service providers) are independent of the businesses or individuals that hire their services. Generally, freelancers work on jobs of a short duration although contract periods do vary in length and can be and are often extended.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Who can become a freelancer?" sub_title="Sub Title 2"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1543562686267{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]The short answer is anyone. There are no restrictions as to who can become a freelancer. As long as you have a skill or service that a business or individual needs then you can offer your services and be a freelancer.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Who hires freelancers?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1543562700159{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Freelancers are hired by individuals and organisations, including micro enterprises, small and medium sized enterprises, large companies, like Tesco, charities, local and central government, e.g., HM Revenue & Customs, and public bodies.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Which services are in demand?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1543562712925{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Demand for services varies but research has shown that the demand for freelance workers increases during times of economic uncertainty. So this is a great time to freelance! Job information sites such as itjobswatch or just searching and counting the number of freelance opportunities can provide useful information on the demand for freelance services.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Where can I freelance?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1543562726185{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]As mentioned, an advantage of freelancing is that it allows you to travel. Depending on your skills and the service you offer, you may work on freelance jobs locally, nationally or internationally. For example, you might offer a gardening service, which would be more likely offered to local individuals and businesses. Or you might freelance as a personal trainer and offer services locally and regionally.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How can I work long hours but avoid burnout?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1543562740168{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]The balance of work and life is one Im forever trying to perfect. In my experience, being self-employed means working longer days than an average job because youre in control of the entire business. On top of that, freelance work can often be unpredictable. Some weeks will be fairly slow while others are overflowing with deadlines to meet. Its critical to be disciplined with your work time for both physical and mental reasons.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1540546427855{background-color: #ff2f54 !important;}"][vc_column text_alignment="text-center" css=".vc_custom_1539601068405{padding-top: 0px !important;}"][havnor_callout call_title="I'm here to lead the way in helping our clients" btn_text="Contact Now" btn_link="#0" open_link="true" btn_text_color="#ffffff" btn_text_hover_color="#ffffff" btn_bg_color="#141334" btn_bg_hover_color="rgba(255,255,255,0.01)" btn_border_color="#141334" btn_border_hover_color="#141334" title_size="28px"][/havnor_callout][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.content:encoded:
Eyeline Creatives

There is something special when creative people get together. Being inexhaustible, life and nature are a constant stimulus for a creative mind. It is the supreme art of the teacher to awaken joy in creative expression and knowledge.

Unique Approach

To create something exceptional, your mindset must be relentlessly focused on the smallest detail. The creation of something new is not accomplished by the intellect but by the play instinct acting from inner necessity. The creative mind plays with the objects it loves. Being inexhaustible, life and nature are a constant stimulus for a creative mind.

Create The Best

It is the supreme art of the teacher to awaken joy in creative expression and knowledge. The uncreative mind can spot wrong answers, but it takes a very creative mind to spot wrong questions.

Being inexhaustible, life and nature are a constant stimulus for a creative mind.

Create The Best
